Aviva Premiership rugby teams look ahead to new season
Media playback is not supported on this deviceThe Aviva Premiership Rugby league is back with Richard Cockerill's reigning champions Leicester Tigers again looking like the team to beat.We hear from Cockerill, plus Newcastle coach Dean Richards who returns to rugby with Harlequinsafter a three-year ban,and Dai Young of London Wasps.Elsewhere,George North will be making his debut for Northamptonafter his big money move from Welsh side Llanelli.